    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="632"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3654. Your 4661, August 5, 3 p. m., fails to give any satisfactory reason for
                    British change in attitude. As tobacco growers have made large plantings in
                    reliance on British assurances that shipments might be made without interference
                    to neutral European ports without regard to ultimate destination and contracts
                    with neutral consignees have been entered into on that basis, Department must
                    insist that pending further discussion British attitude, assurance of
                    non-interference be given with reference to all contracts entered into <hi
                        rend="italic">bona fide</hi> before notice change attitude on part Great
                    Britain and that these shipments may go forward without consignment Netherlands
                    Oversea Trust.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
